<TITLE> 7 Bangladeshi call centres join UK expo </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 15 (bdnews24.com)  Seven Bangladeshi firms are joining the two-day Call Centre Expo 2008 in the UK, beginning Tuesday. The seven firms are Aamra Outsourcing Ltd, HMC Technology Ltd, InGen Technology, Iqra Media Centre, Legato Services Ltd, Orbit Communications and Windmill Advertising Ltd. BTRC chairman Manzurul Alam, telecoms secretary Iqbal Mahmood, and Kamal Uddin, executive chairman of the Board of Investment, are in Birmingham city to visit the show. Participation at the show is aimed at attracting foreign clients, a senior official at Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission said. The official at the BTRC's media wing said the government would help the call centres participate in more such expos in future. The BTRC started giving licence for call centre in April. The telecom regulator issued 310 licenxes in three categories  Call Centre, Hosted Call Centre and Hosed Call Centre Service Provider. bdn
